data.description: PRICE REDUCED, PLUS buyer incentive options available: $8,000 towards closing costs, fencing, appliances, rate buy down, whatever the buyer needs!! // Welcome to 637 Pollyanna Drive, a traditional two-story home situated on a flat lot in a great and growing neighborhood. Located in the lower part of Greenville, this central location allows for easy access to the interstate, Mauldin, Simpsonville, and the rest of Greenville. Harrington is a newer community with a variety of builders and styles, featuring two pools, firepits, playground, and lots of common area green space. Inside the home you will find a welcoming, open layout on the first floor with both a dining room (could be used as an office, sitting room, etc.) and breakfast nook. Upstairs are three bedrooms (all with walk-in closets), two bathrooms, and a large laundry room. The master bedroom features dual master walk-in closets, and the master bath offer dual vanities, tiled shower, and separate tub. The backyard is flat and open, borders easement space for extra breathing room, and features a patio space for outdoor living. One BIG note about this house, which is only three years old, is that it used to be the MODEL HOME and thus features A TON of upgrades. Some examples include: all countertops in the home are quartz, tile backsplash in kitchen, upgraded kitchen cabinets including extras on the kitchen island, added crown molding and wainscotting, upgraded LVT/LVP flooring in all common areas, tiled master bath shower, tray ceiling in the master bedroom, and a gas fireplace. Don’t wait! Come check out this fantastic property today, just in time for the holidays!
